#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:survey.survey,description:esg_csrd.esg_metric_review_template
msgid ""
"Welcome to this CSRD Double Materiality Stakeholder Review, <br><br>\n"
"                    You've been asked to participate to a CSRD Metric "
"Review. <br><br>\n"
"                    We are looking for your input on how the company impacts "
"the environment and how these impacts could affect the company financially."
msgstr ""
"Welkom bij deze CSRD Dubbele materialiteitsbeoordeling voor stakeholders, "
"<br><br>\n"
"                    Je wordt uitgenodigd om deel te nemen aan een CSRD "
"Indicatorbeoordeling. <br><br>\n"
"                    We zijn benieuwd naar je mening over de impact van het "
"bedrijf op het milieu en hoe deze impact het bedrijf financieel zou kunnen "
"beïnvloeden."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:esg_csrd.res_config_settings_view_form
msgid ""
"When enabled, ESRS metrics, double materiality assessment, stakeholder "
"review, and the sustainability report are added."
msgstr ""
"Als dit is ingeschakeld worden ESRS-indicatoren, dubbele "
"materialiteitsbeoordeling, stakeholderbeoordeling en het "
"duurzaamheidsrapport toegevoegd."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid ""
"When indirect data sources or estimates have been used (e.g., industry\n"
"                        averages or supplier data models), the basis for "
"such estimations is clearly\n"
"                        indicated in the respective topic sections."
msgstr ""
"Wanneer indirecte gegevensbronnen of schattingen zijn gebruikt (bv.\n"
"                        sectorgemiddelden of datamodellen van leveranciers), "
"wordt de basis voor deze schattingen duidelijk\n"
"                        aangegeven in de betreffende hoofdstukken."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid ""
"When specific sustainability topics deviate from these default time "
"horizons\n"
"                        (e.g., climate-related targets extending beyond 10 "
"years), the rationale is\n"
"                        provided in the respective disclosure section."
msgstr ""
"Wanneer specifieke duurzaamheidsonderwerpen afwijken van deze standaard "
"tijdshorizonten (bv. klimaatdoelstellingen die verder reiken dan 10 jaar), "
"wordt de onderbouwing hiervan vermeld in de betreffende sectie."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_metrics_targets
msgid ""
"Where applicable, both absolute and intensity-based data are disclosed to\n"
"                        ensure\n"
"                        comparability and transparency."
msgstr ""
"Waar van toepassing worden zowel absolute als op intensiteit gebaseerde "
"gegevens verstrekt om vergelijkbaarheid en transparantie te waarborgen."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_environmental_a
msgid ""
"Where automated measurement is not available, data are estimated using "
"emission\n"
"                factors or mass balance methods consistent with the EU "
"Industrial Emissions\n"
"                Directive (IED) or ISO 14064 guidelines."
msgstr ""
"Waar geautomatiseerde meting niet beschikbaar is, worden gegevens geschat "
"met behulp van emissiefactoren of massabalansmethoden die consistent zijn "
"met de EU-richtlijn industriële emissies (IED) of ISO 14064-richtlijnen."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_governance_c
msgid ""
"Where complete data are unavailable, estimates are based on the scope of "
"governance\n"
"                oversight, sample audits, or extrapolation from comparable "
"business units."
msgstr ""
"Wanneer volledige gegevens niet beschikbaar zijn, worden schattingen "
"gebaseerd op de reikwijdte van het toezicht op de governance, "
"steekproefaudits of extrapolatie van vergelijkbare bedrijfseenheden."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_social_b
msgid ""
"Where data gaps exist, disclose estimation techniques and\n"
"                                    sources."
msgstr ""
"Maak bij ontbrekende gegevens de schattingstechnieken en gegevensbronnen "
"bekend."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_social_b
msgid "Where data gaps exist, disclose estimation techniques and data sources."
msgstr ""
"Maak bij ontbrekende gegevens de schattingstechnieken en gegevensbronnen "
"bekend."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_social_b
msgid ""
"Where direct data are unavailable, estimates are derived from sample "
"surveys,\n"
"                        historical trends, or modeled ratios based on "
"comparable products, services,\n"
"                        or regions."
msgstr ""
"Wanneer directe gegevens niet beschikbaar zijn, worden schattingen afgeleid "
"van steekproefenquêtes, historische trends of gemodelleerde verhoudingen op "
"basis van vergelijkbare producten, diensten of regio's."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid ""
"Where quantitative metrics are based on estimates, approximations, or "
"partial\n"
"                        data coverage, the methodology and assumptions are "
"explained in the\n"
"                        corresponding disclosure notes."
msgstr ""
"Wanneer kwantitatieve maatstaven zijn gebaseerd op schattingen, benaderingen "
"of gedeeltelijke datadekking, worden de methodologie en aannames toegelicht "
"in de bijbehorende toelichtingen."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_social_b
msgid ""
"Where relevant, consumer-related indicators (e.g., complaints, product\n"
"                        recalls, satisfaction scores, privacy compliance) "
"undergo external assurance\n"
"                        in line with recognized frameworks such as ISO 9001, "
"ISO 26000, AA1000\n"
"                        Assurance Standard, or regulatory audits."
msgstr ""
"Waar relevant ondergaan consumentengerelateerde indicatoren (bv. klachten, "
"terugroepacties, tevredenheidsscores, naleving van privacywetgeving) externe "
"assurance in lijn met erkende kaders zoals ISO 9001, ISO 26000, de AA1000 "
"Assurance Standard of audits door toezichthouders."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_governance_c
msgid ""
"Where relevant, governance indicators (e.g., confirmed corruption incidents, "
"policy\n"
"                coverage, ethical training completion) undergo external "
"assurance using recognized\n"
"                frameworks such as ISO 37001, AA1000 Assurance Standard, or "
"national audit\n"
"                standards."
msgstr ""
"Waar relevant ondergaan governance-indicatoren (bv. bevestigde corruptie-"
"incidenten, beleidsdekking, voltooiing van ethische trainingen) externe "
"assurance met behulp van erkende kaders zoals ISO 37001, de AA1000 Assurance "
"Standard of nationale auditnormen."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_iro_management
msgid ""
"Where relevant, references are included to external standards or\n"
"                        initiatives the company aligns with."
msgstr ""
"Waar relevant wordt verwezen naar externe standaarden of initiatieven "
"waarbij de onderneming zich aansluit."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_social_b
msgid ""
"Where relevant, workforce indicators (e.g., diversity, pay equity, safety)\n"
"                undergo external assurance in line with recognized "
"frameworks such as <strong>ISAE\n"
"                3000</strong>, <strong>GRI 401-404</strong>, or <strong>ILO "
"labor standards</strong>\n"
"                ."
msgstr ""
"Waar relevant ondergaan personeelsindicatoren (bv. diversiteit, "
"loonbillijkheid, veiligheid) externe assurance in lijn met erkende kaders "
"zoals <strong>ISAE 3000</strong>, <strong>GRI 401-404</strong> of de "
"<strong>arbeidsnormen van de ILO</strong>."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid ""
"Where reporting systems are still being harmonized, integration of\n"
"                        sustainability data collection, consolidation, and "
"internal control\n"
"                        procedures is targeted for completion by "
"<strong>[<em>insert target year</em>]</strong>."
msgstr ""
"Waar rapportagesystemen nog worden geharmoniseerd, wordt gestreefd naar "
"voltooiing van de integratie van\n"
"                        procedures voor het verzamelen, de consolidatie en "
"het intern controleren van\n"
"                        duurzaamheidsgegevens tegen <strong>[<em>voeg "
"doeljaar in</em>]</strong>."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid ""
"Where such topics have been assessed as <strong>material</strong>,\n"
"                                the entity should still provide a "
"<strong>summary of relevant\n"
"                                impacts, policies,\n"
"                                    actions, and metrics</strong>."
msgstr ""
"Wanneer dergelijke onderwerpen als <strong>materieel</strong> zijn "
"beoordeeld, dient de entiteit alsnog een <strong>samenvatting te geven van "
"de relevante effecten, het beleid, de acties en de maatstaven</strong>."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid "Which standards are partially or fully omitted"
msgstr "Welke standaarden geheel of gedeeltelijk zijn weggelaten"

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_appendix_governance_c
msgid "Whistleblowing and grievance reporting platforms."
msgstr "Klokkenluidersregelingen of feedbackkanalen."

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_esrs_s1
msgid "Whistleblowing or feedback channels"
msgstr "Klokkenluiders- of feedbackkanalen"

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_basic_for_prepation
msgid "Within 1 year"
msgstr "Binnen 1 jaar"

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_esrs_s1
msgid "Women in top-level management"
msgstr "Vrouwen in topmanagement"

#. module: esg_csrd
#: model_terms:knowledge.article,template_body:esg_csrd.esg_csrd_knowledge_article_template_csrd_esrs_s1
msgid "Women in workforce"
msgstr "Vrouwen in het personeelsbestand"

